The paper discusses the impact of BatchNorm on the loss landscape of multi-layer networks consisting of fully-connected and convolutional layers. This topic is highly relevant to the fields of machine learning and computer vision, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.CL. Among these, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the topic of the paper. The other categories are also relevant, as they cover topics such as neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are all related to the use of BatchNorm in modern neural network architectures.
